    "question": "How many sides has a regular polygon whose interior angle is 135°?",
    "option": {
      "a": "12",
      "b": "10",
      "c": "9",
      "d": "8",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "d",
    "solution": "If each interior angle of the polygon is 135°, then each exterior angle is 180° - 135° = 45°.\n\nHence, number of sides =\n\n360°/one exterior angle\n\n\n360°/45°\n\n\n= 8",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2014"
